b'' b'\\input amstex' b'\\documentstyle{amsppt}' b'\\pagewidth{6.5in}' b'\\magnification=1200' b'\\pageheight{7.5in}' b'\\' b'\\title {letter to the editor} \\endtitle' b'\\author {matthew l. fante} \\endauthor' b'\\date {april \\enddate' b'\\endtopmatter' b'' b'in a letter to the fbi, david koresh said: ``do you want me to' b"pull back the heavens and show you my anger?! fear me.'' the day" b'standoff between federal agents and the branch davidians ended on april b'in what appeared to be a mass suicide by fire. now that the multi-million' b'dollar standoff is over, a few things remain: cleaning up the mess, and' b'assigning blame.' b'' b'\\' b'' b'from the onset of the april tear gas attacks by federal agents, president' b'clinton already started passing the buck by saying ``talk to the attorney' b'general or the fbi... i knew it was going to be done, but the decision was' b"{\\it entirely theirs}. {\\it they} made the tactical decision.'' enter" b'attorney general janet reno. after most of the branch davidians died,' b"reno said she took ``full responsibility'' for the decision. ``i approved" b"the plan'' she said adding that she ``did not advise him [clinton] as to the" b"details.'' in fact, she told clinton that it was ``the best way to go.''" b"as the fire was roaring through the branch davidian's compound clinton said" b"that he was ``deeply sadened by the loss of life'' and in the same breath that" b'``the law enforcement agencies involved in the waco siege recommended the' b"course of action pursued today.'' later he went on to say ``i stand by that" b"[reno's] decision.''" b'' b'\\' b'' b'how did this all begin? at on february agents of the bureau of' b'alcohol, tobacco and firearms (batf) launched a full-scale, high-profile' b"assault on the branch davidian's compound. this raid was much" b'more than an assault on a group suspected of possessing illegal weapons. the' b'assault was a planned media circus used as a propaganda device of the batf' b'to show their might and just purpose.' b'' b'\\' b'' b"at the onset of the ``no-knock'' raid, gaggles of heavily armed batf agents" b'made their way inside the compound without identifying themselves or state' b'that they had a warrant until long after the shooting began.' b"silently, the agents made their way to the compound's buildings and started" b"their ``search'' by charging at the buildings and throwing concussion grenades" b'and ordering the cult members to come out of the buildings.' b'' b'\\' b'' b'if unknown persons dressed in black ninja costumes and combat fatigues' b'were to attack you, throwing grenades and brandishing firearms, would you not' b'assume that these people are criminals and attempt to defend yourself? the' b'tactics employed by the batf provoked the battle.' b'' b'\\' b'' b'the initial assualt by the batf was not successful. unfortunately, lives' b'were lost on both sides. but, had the assault been a success, the liberal' b'media would have praised the batf by showing the footage of batf agents' b'carting away a bunch of gun-wielding religious nuts. of course, any' b"violation of the cult's rights would have been overlooked and the media" b"would proclaim america's fortune in having super-cop organizations like the" b"batf that can systematically ``take out'' terroristic groups such as the" b'branch davidians.' b'' b'\\' b'' b'as far as i can see, the batf and the fbi dropped the ball just like' b'philadelphia did in the move crisis which left dead, homeless,' b'and a city block razed.' b'it appears that the batf has adopted the shoot-first tactic of no-knock' b"raids to execute search warrants. don't let the batf convince you that" b'the no-knock raid was justified. no-knock assaults make sense when looking' b'for, say, drugs that can easily be hidden or disposed of in a few seconds.' b'the batf was looking for illegal weapons, not drugs that could be hidden or' b'flushed down the toilet in a matter of a few seconds. what ever happened to' b"``this is the police! you are surrounded...''? {\\it this policy of no-knock" b'raids, by federal and local agencies, should be restricted}. further, the use' b'of military firepower against presumed innocent citizens is a very scary idea,' b'and is why the davidians were justified in using lethal force to ensure that' b'their fourth ammendment rights [``the right of the people to be secure in' b'their persons, houses, papers, and effects, against unreasonable searches' b"and seizures''] are not denied." b'' b'\\' b'' b'\\' b'' b'\\' b'' b'\\noindent matthew l. fante \\newline' b'\\end' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'--' b'____________________________________________________________________' b'matthew fante' b'' b'410 webster street a public key is available' b'bethlehem pa upon request' 